The Scorched Wastes

Formerly the Meridian Intake March: a toll corridor with pavilions, cistern regulators, and charter stations. Now a burn-scarred desert of glassed dunes, collapsed ruins, and undead bureaucrats.

Cause of destruction: the failed Ninth Meridian Rite attempted to fuse solar measurement with underworld descent authority. Systems desynchronized. Heat surged through dry water channels. Sustained burn wave glassed dunes, collapsed structures, and created undead administrative persistence.

Three factions contest the ruins. Charter Remnants: descendants of intake clerks, mix of living survivalists and undead functionaries who demand documents and attack when paperwork is missing. Dune Host Reavers: logistics predators who inherited route knowledge from ruined records, hoard water and legal tablets. Synod Eclipse Cells: religious faction that believes the failed synthesis can be corrected, stages mock tribunals and witness-burning rites.

Hostile ecology includes scorpion broods in collapsed embalming halls. Faultline entities (heat echoes, salt-lung shades, pressure phantoms) manifest near dry governor mechanisms, distorting sound and direction.

Shares thermal origin with Saltglass Reach to the east. The same burn pulse propagated through the dry Iseth channel at reduced intensity, fusing the Reach's sand into glass. The Wastes took full force; the Reach got the echo.

Rooms reflect former administrative purposes repurposed after collapse: verdict halls held by revenants, toll stones recut as curses, ration seals worn as raider insignia.

