The Scorched Wastes -- Mafdet Perspective

Quarantine Ledger maintains a standing exclusion order on all Wastes cargo. Classification: Collapsed Attestation Zone, Tier Four -- highest hazard designation. The Wastes are a dead trade district still issuing documents.

Formerly the Meridian Intake March. Mafdet's Ledger Houses received goods from this corridor with clean provenance. The Ninth Meridian Rite failed and the burn wave turned a trade corridor into a glass-and-ash necropolis.

Primary concern: persistence of process without legitimacy. Undead Charter Remnants still demand documents and issue citations at checkpoints connecting to no functioning authority. The Shrine of the First Claw recognizes no oath sworn to a dead institution. This is oath-breaking of the deepest kind: law's form maintained after its substance has died.

Dune Host Reavers mimic attestation but carry no authority Mafdet's Ledger Houses accept. When Reaver-handled cargo reaches the Saltglass Reach, Mafdet assessors strip all prior documentation and re-attest from scratch. Cost falls on the carrier.

Synod Eclipse Cells conducting mock tribunals are the Quarantine Ledger's worst case: religious authority filling the void of collapsed civic process. Their recut inscriptions occasionally appear on cargo containers reaching Mafdet's port. Destroyed on sight.

The Wastes share origin with Mafdet's own Saltglass Reach. The same thermal pulse, attenuated by distance, created the glass flats. What burned the Wastes glazed Mafdet's doorstep.

Every guardian-name sworn at the Shrine carries an implicit clause: Mafdet will not become what the Wastes became. Process without accountability. Oaths enforced by the dead against the living. The Quarantine Ledger exists because the Wastes proved documentation alone is not enough.
